        <h3 data-uuid="40df4e5872f24eb2898210042ee288b2">Wilson’s Reforms</h3>
        <p data-uuid="f79d442ab67c4523a7793600415c8c75">In his inaugural address, Wilson spoke of the terrible social conditions of many working-class Americans. He said that it was not enough to applaud the country’s industrial achievements, but Americans must attend to the needs of the workers. Passing reform legislation was Wilson’s top goal. He pushed for two measures soon after taking office: tariff revision and banking reform.<br />
        </p>
