        <p data-uuid="9d0480e3fadb4f1cb47132e899834e43">Wilson also pushed for laws to regulate big business. The Clayton Antitrust Act of 1914 strengthened federal laws against monopolies. The Federal Trade Commission, created in 1914, had the power to investigate and punish unfair trade practices. Wilson’s success in guiding reform programs through Congress helped him to win re-election in 1916.</p>
